Did you try known good BIOS?
Any history available?
can you send me a good bios file for this machine
I already tried this bios, the problem continues, I see that with the thermal camera pch 62 degrees, it is very hot when touched, is it possible that it is damaged?
"Any history available? I see like a liquid in this section, attached photos
There may be accumulated crap under some BGA chip.
then what step to follow does an wash board with ultrasonic cleaner?
Try first heating PCH and CPU with quality flux; supposing to have accumulated crap underneath.
WHAT TEMPERATURE AND HOW MANY TIME?

You have 1 year on the forum and many threads about that on the forum.
Take notes and save time...

180-200 degrees, 15-20s; no need to melt the balls.
Excuse me, I don't practice this procedure much, I'm going to make a note. I've already done the procedure. The problem persists. Anything else I can do?

Hello, I recently bought an ultrasonic cleaner crest powersonic p1200h machine and following the advice of the forum, I would like to ask you something when using the branson ec  with distilled water, solution, how many washes is this used for boards solution, or how long can the solution be left unused?
I am ultrasonic washing time 2 minutes on each side is that ok?
si depronto no me hize entender, para cuantas limpiezas de board me alcanza la solucion(ec branson y agua destilada), o por cuanto tiempo me funciona la solucion, o hay que cambiar inmediatamente depues de una lavada?

No need to change the cleaner solution so fast.
You should appreciate by eye, when to change it.

Run 5-10 min on each side.
Be aware, if no sweep function available, move a bit the board every 30-60s.
This avoid host spots, which can damage traces, or components.

Use an electric heater to preheat the liquid; 60-70 degrees C should be good.
Embedded heater on the machine takes lot of time and probably never reaches such temp.
